DO-NUT interrupt me when I’m at my table with another student. (This is my “trying to be patient and kind but I’m being driven slightly crazy” teacher face.

It is almost October… And this little moment in our morning meeting is one of the ways I can tell!  Self-control. It is a super hard thing to master…Especially in kindergarten!  I am a teacher who likes to have BIG FUN— but because of that, I have to be sure I can get things back under control quickly! 😅 I have started saying the phrase “BIG FUN!” and they say “NOW we’re done!” It allows us to have moments of controlled silly chaos…which I love!  Can you relate? 🙃

Teaching kindergarten has meant so very much to me these past 10 years.  Quite frankly, it’s been the vehicle that has uncovered pieces of me I didn’t know existed. 

✨The friends I’ve made are lifelong. 
✨The lessons I’ve learned are many. 
✨The laughter is pretty much never-ending in kindergarten. (I mean…there’s a lot more than that—but the laughter overrides it all!) 

I was absolutely honored to be awarded one of @nashvillepef Blue Ribbon Teachers this year. And even better?  I got to accept it alongside two teammates @abby__day and @ashae79 , friends and educators I deeply admire from the school I love, @lockelanddesigncenter. 

Congrats to all the MNPS teachers this year!! 👏🏻✨

🚨SURPRISE! A bonus episode of Happiest Hour Podcast just dropped. My very special guest is the fabulous chart-topping children’s music artist and children’s book author, Kaci Bolls! 

➡️ Type the word KACI into comments and we’ll send you the link in your DM’s  to listen to the podcast or watch it on YouTube! 

Read on to find out more about Kaci and the FAN GIVEAWAY! One of you lucky listeners will win a signed copy of her new children’s book + a swag pack with stickers, a pin and bookmark! 🎉

For decades, Kaci Bolls has been a sought after Nashville session singer and songwriter. When life nudged her to do an about-face, get her Master’s Degree in education and become a kindergarten teacher, Kaci found a way to combine her love of music and kindergarteners by releasing chart-topping hits of original children’s music. Based on her song, “Dare to Be Me,” Kaci has recently released a children’s book by the same name. 

In this episode, we discuss:

• How she went from a top Nashville singer/songwriter to kindergarten teacher (and being awarded “Teacher of the Year,” nonetheless)

• What propelled her to start making chart-topping children’s music

• Coming to terms with how she was holding herself back (but NO more!)

• The #1 message she wants kids to know, and the theme of her new book, Dare to Be Me

...and so much more!

It’s all waiting for you: the episode, the book giveaway, and the delicious weekend recipes we include in each podcast. ✨ Just type KACI in comments, then check your DM’s! 

#podcast #happiesthour #happiesthourpodcast #kacibolls #kacbollskids #childrensbook #childrensauthor #weekendrecipe #cocktailhour #happyhour #beinspired

The Calloway County Public Library will host its first CCPL Saturday Special Event on Saturday, October 28, from 10:30-11:30 AM in CCPL’s Community Room.

Children of all ages, accompanied by an adult, are invited to a fun-filled program featuring Kaci Bolls & Nathan Meckel, the multi-talented authors of the newly published children’s book Dare to Be Me.  Following the program, participants will have an opportunity to meet the authors and purchase books.

The program is presented free of charge.  No registration is required.  For more information, please email contactccpl@callowaycountylibrary.org.

So…what are you thankful for? 👇🏻

🎵 Last night my brother and I went to see @sncmusic at @theryman in Nashville, Tn…and IT WAS SOOOO GOOOOD!!!! 

More than Several reasons why:
1.  Two of my past kinders’ dad is in it and he is GREAT! @mikeluginbill 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻
2.  A capella music is our bread and butter…what we grew up on and we LOVE it.
3.  The medleys, the humor, the flow of all the guys….SUPERB. Check out their music!!! 🎄New holiday tunes you NEED! 
4.  When we walked up…this crew I love — all past kinders of mine — greeted me like I was their long lost bestie.  I LOVE THEM. 
5.  I heard, “Kaci Shannon” two rows back and instantly knew who it was. @carrawaykc I love you!💕
6.  I just love hangin’ with my lil bro…even when he gives me a shadow beard (see pic) @jeremybolls 

Thank you @zoejamail!! You are the best.  We are official new fans! 😘 I have no pictures of the actual show because I was so in the moment!

✨ In the hardest of times, a little act of kindness can go a long way to lighten and brighten a day. 

🤔 Don’t believe me?  Case in point:
I’ve had some frustrating hip issues as of late…not ideal for a kindergarten teacher. 
✨ @kindermartin13 brought down a spare rolling chair
✨ @dpetrelli has rolled me to my car pick up each day
✨ @maestra_guzman has come to my class to pick up my kids rather than have me walk there 
✨ @ammanarie delivered my kids to me after art class 
✨ @jaclyn.boles.98 has let my kids tag into the end of her line going to lunch and recess while I slow poke along 
✨ my kids…..have been ROCKSTARS. Passing out things for me—being extra patient—giving me hugs and making jokes with me
I could go on and on…

🙏🏻 ALL of this has been offered—I’ve not asked a single soul.  It’s inspiring.  My mom always said if you are feeling down in the dumps, look up, look out, and find something small to do for someone else.  To be a recipient is humbling. 

💡 The holiday season can be extra hard for so many people, on so many different levels, for so many different reasons.  Let us all seek to be a little light to someone else. 

(I can’t remember what teacher made this—but if it’s you—we love it!)

💕 One of my favorite things in kindergarten is our month-long gingerbread unit—where we compare and contrast book after book after book!  Did you know there are about as many versions of gingerbread cookies out there as there are books?  Yup!  We gather up every one of them we can find—and do a little taste test each day after we read our book.  At the end we’ll vote on our favorite!  Personally…this homemade batch that arrived may take claim first prize! 🏆

📖 Do you have a favorite gingerbread book?  Do tell!  I think I have collected all of them—but always excited to find a new one!

So…last year I decided (without much thought) that I’d turn into a gingerbread man and explode out of the bathroom (oven) door to surprise my kinders.  As they stared at me, wide-eyed, I panicked and instinctively yelled “RUN RUN as fast as you CAN!” and bolted out of the classroom.  I headed straight to the gym…20 screaming 5-year-olds trailing close behind. We had quite the chasing frenzy — complete with our PE teacher, dragging me across the floor by my little gingerbread legs. 

As I contemplate all of the many decisions I have made over the years in the “movement” department that may or may not have contributed to the necessity of my full hip replacement in a couple weeks…this moment comes to mind. 

I mean…teaching aerobics on concrete floors in the early 90s may have contributed as well.  But it’s more likely that the chemicals in my Bon Jovi-esque perm just altered my ability to make sane decisions.  Alas…we may  never know. 

👵🏼🩼 This year I’ll be playing the part of the old lady who baked the gingerbread man. My goal is to revive my gingerbread run in 2024! 😅
